Cross Site Scripting vulnerability allows an attacker to interfere with the interactions that users have with the vulnerable web application. 
It allows an attacker to circumvent the same origin policy which is designed to segregate different websites from each other.

Reflected XSS, when the malicious script comes from the current HTTP request.
Stored XSS, when the malicious script comes from the application server/database.
DOM XSS, when the malicious script is present in the client side rather than from server side code.
